<div xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>The MFN Site defined master file notification transaction is used where the master file is not a simple one (as defined for MFN^M13) and is not a transaction type currently defined by HL7, but rather requires one or more HL7 and/or 'Z' segments to carry the master file information.</p>
</div>
<div id="v2-classic-content" style="display:none;">
<p>The full structure definition for <a href="StructureDefinition-MFN_Znn.html">MFN_Znn</a> is available on its own page.</p>
